    "See figure 6.",
    "We do have the freedom of rescaling 2 D (h) 0 independently for all h ∈ H L, but this only modifies the × factors in (23) by replacing σ by a different representative σ ′ of [σ].We can also study similar properties for some other line operator L [g] in the multiplet M L. It is easy to see that the induced 0-form symmetry on L [g] is H L [g]:= g H L g -1 which is isomorphic to H L and the 't Hooft anomaly of the H L [g] induced 0-form symmetry is obtained by simply transporting [σ] by the isomorphism between H L and H L [g]."
